article.headline: UT-Pan American stings Grand Canyon 73-72
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas -- Elijah Watson drove for a contested jump shot with about two seconds left, lifting Texas-Pan American to a 73-72 victory and foiling a Grand Canyon comeback bid Saturday night. UT-Pan American's Dan Kimasa stole the ball as Grand Canyon tried to inbound, leading to Watson's winning 3-footer. Ryan Majerle hit a 3-pointer, sparking an 11-5 run as Grand Canyon, which trailed most of the game, rallied in the final minutes to lead 72-70 on a DeWayne Russell layup with 12 seconds left. The Antelopes (11-10, 2-2) lost their second straight in Western Athletic Conference play after falling to New Mexico on Thursday. Shaquille Hines and Shaquille Boga scored 18 each for Texas-Pan American (8-13, 2-3) and Janari Joesaar added 16 points with 11 rebounds. Watson finished with seven points and six assists -- both career highs. Joshua Braun scored a career-high 25 for the Antelopes, Russell added 15 and Majerle 13.
